======================================================================
Part 3: Simplicial Euler characteristic
chi(Delta_{n-1}) = sum (-1)^p C(n,p+1) = 1
======================================================================
  n=2: chi(Delta_1) = sum (-1)^p C(2,p+1) = 1
  n=3: chi(Delta_2) = sum (-1)^p C(3,p+1) = 1
  n=4: chi(Delta_3) = sum (-1)^p C(4,p+1) = 1
  n=5: chi(Delta_4) = sum (-1)^p C(5,p+1) = 1
  n=6: chi(Delta_5) = sum (-1)^p C(6,p+1) = 1
  n=7: chi(Delta_6) = sum (-1)^p C(7,p+1) = 1
  n=8: chi(Delta_7) = sum (-1)^p C(8,p+1) = 1
  n=9: chi(Delta_8) = sum (-1)^p C(9,p+1) = 1

======================================================================
Part 4: chi(T) - 1 distribution (topological defect)
chi(T) = 1: topologically simplex-like (contractible)
chi(T) = 0: homologically non-trivial
======================================================================

